"Lepert P., Brillet F.","The overall effects of road works on global warming gas emissions",2009,"Transportation Research Part D: Transport and Environment","14","8",,"576","584",,,10.1016/j.trd.2009.08.002,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-71449114933&partnerID=40&md5=031ca6e9ec916260001bd7c85c6d4569","Division of Road Maintenance, Safety and Acoustics, Laboratoire Central des Ponts et Chaussées, 44340 Bouguenais, France; Laboratoire Central des Ponts et Chaussées, 44340 Bouguenais, France","Lepert, P., Division of Road Maintenance, Safety and Acoustics, Laboratoire Central des Ponts et Chaussées, 44340 Bouguenais, France; Brillet, F., Laboratoire Central des Ponts et Chaussées, 44340 Bouguenais, France","Road characteristics influence the amount of pollution generated by traffic. They govern the rolling resistance, which includes: the viscoelastic behaviour of the pavement structure, surface texture, and profile unevenness. Road works are performed on a periodic basis to maintain these characteristics at proper levels of service (e.g. safety, comfort, and noise). While such works produce additional pollution (due to congestion around worksites or extra fuel consumption along the detour route), they still result in less pollution over the long term. This article assesses the balance between an increase in gas emissions during road works and the reduction in emissions from traffic once the works are completed. It is demonstrated that when road works are introduced to correct longitudinal profiles, rather than texture, the emissions benefit is substantial.","Atmospheric pollution; Gas emissions; Road characteristics; Road transport","Atmospheric pollution; Detour route; Global warming gas emissions; Long term; Longitudinal profile; Pavement structures; Road transports; Surface textures; Viscoelastic behaviour; Air pollution; Atmospheric movements; Aviation; Global warming; Leakage (fluid); Roads and streets; Surface structure; Textures; Truck transportation; Gas emissions; atmospheric pollution; global warming; road construction; road transport; traffic emission",,,,,,"André, J.-M., Vehicle emission measurement collection of the Artemis database (2005) Artemis 3312 Report, Ref 0504, INRETS-LTE, , Paris; Brillet, F., (2007) Vers une approche technico-économique de l'entretien des routes, , Laboratoire Central des Ponts et Chaussées, Etudes et Recherches, coll. Routes et sécurité routière, Paris; Brillet, F., Vadepied, C., (2007) Mesures et modélisation de la consommation en carburant sur un véhicule léger. Contrat ANR PROPICE, , Laboratoire Central des Ponts et Chaussées, Paris; Brillet, F., Vadepied, C., Consequences of pavement maintenance works on fuel consumption and greenhouse effect gas emission (2007) World Road Congress, , Paris; Brillet, F., Vadepied, C., (2009) Modèle de calcul de la gêne subie par les usagers lors des chantiers d'entretien routier, , Agence Nationale de la Recherche, contrat PROPICE, Brussels; (2007) Statutes Effective January 2007, Integrated Waste Management Board, , Californian Environmental Protection Agency, Californian Environmental Protection Agency, Sacremento; (2007) EU Energy and Transport in Figures, , European Commission, Directorate General for Energy and Transport, European Commission, Brussels; (2008) Work Programme 2008 - Cooperation - THEME 7 - Transport (including aeronautics), , European Commission, European Commission, Brussels; A study of the use of recycled paving material (1993) Report to Congress as specified in the Intermodal Surface Transportation Efficiency Act of 1991, , Federal Highways Administration, ISTEA, Report No. FHWA, RD, 93, 147, EPA/600/R-93/095. Washington DC; Hildebrand, G., Lepert, P., Development of models for the economic evaluation of pavement maintenance: The PAV-ECO project (1999) 2nd European Research Conference, , Brussels; Jullien, A., Ventura, A., avril-mai 2007. L'analyse du cycle de vie (ACV) appliquée aux routes: apports et limita